Resolve enumeration warnings

Resetting SUDPTRCTL to Auto Mode in handle_get_descriptor (as other parts of
the firmware may clear it).

The following errors were reported by Linux:

  reset high-speed USB device number 13 using ehci-pci
  usb 1-1.1.6: device descriptor read/64; error 2
  usb 1-1.1.6: device descriptor read/64; error 2

Eventually Linux will stop enumerating the device at all; with an error
such as:

  unable to enumerate USB device on port 6
Install doxygen & rubber and build the docs.

Merge pull request #21 from StefanBruens/master

Cleanup of autovector interrupt code

Avoid multiple evaluation of argument to RESETTOGGLE macro

If the argument evaluation has side effects; the expansion has unwanted
effects. Also the evaluation may be expensive (e.g. fetching data from
a volatile register).
The new code can be better optimized by sdcc; and avoids fetching contents
from the volatile TOGCTL register.

replace USB/GPIF autovector asm code with normal interrupt

The jump table is target for both the USB as the GPIF interrupt. Including
autovector.h references the _gpif_isr/_usb_isr symbols and forces linking
of the jump table.
